When one configures an LDAP configuration, you can seemingly choose to do either User or Group, and both.
I would like to suggest adding a checkbox before each of these sections in the UI which defines if the settings will be used in the function or not.
Right now this is not clear, and also this perpetuates a bug which I have just submitted where the LDAP code seems to hang on a misconfigured group DN that prevents Confluence from writing into local groups. This could be avoided if the code knew it should not use the group settings (when its grouping is not checked) in addition to fixing the bug that in case the group DN is wrong, it won't write at all.

